**Workflow:**
User -> Planner;
Planner -> WebSearcher;
WebSearcher -> Summarizer;
Summarizer -> End.

**Description:**
First, the Planner analyzes the query and creates a step-by-step search strategy to identify (1) the specific dinosaur-related Featured Article promoted in November 2016 on English Wikipedia and (2) its nominator. Second, the WebSearcher executes this plan via sequential web searches, iterating as needed to refine results. Finally, the Summarizer integrates the findings into a precise answer.
